<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="141" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,224,538]" pageId="4" pageNumber="141">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,260,224,250]" pageId="4" pageNumber="141">Remarks</emphasis>
. The spelling of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wright" authorityYear="1869" box="[451,566,224,249]" class="Anthozoa" family="Isididae" genus="Keratoisis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Alcyonacea" pageId="4" pageNumber="141" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[451,566,224,249]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="141">Keratoisis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was changed to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Verrill" authorityYear="1883" box="[754,869,224,250]" class="Anthozoa" family="Isididae" genus="Ceratoisis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Alcyonacea" pageId="4" pageNumber="141" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[754,869,224,250]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="141">Ceratoisis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Verrill, A. E." box="[912,1065,224,250]" pageId="4" pageNumber="141" pagination="1 - 72" refId="ref9372" refString="Verrill, A. E. (1883) Report on the Anthozoa, and on some additional species dredged by the &quot; Blake &quot; in 1877 - 1879, and by the U. S. Fish Commission Steamer &quot; Fish Hawk &quot; in 1880 - 82. Bulletin of the Museum of Comparative Zoology, 11, 1 - 72." type="journal article" year="1883">Verrill (1883)</bibRefCitation>
based on his transliteration from Greek. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Verrill" authorityYear="1883" box="[235,350,260,286]" class="Anthozoa" family="Isididae" genus="Ceratoisis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Alcyonacea" pageId="4" pageNumber="141" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[235,350,260,286]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="141">Ceratoisis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was then used until 
<bibRefCitation author="Bayer, F. M." box="[585,735,259,286]" pageId="4" pageNumber="141" refId="ref8947" refString="Bayer, F. M. (1956) Octocorallia. Treatise on Invertebrate Paleontology, Part F, F 166 - F 231." type="journal volume" year="1956">Bayer (1956)</bibRefCitation>
reverted to the original. The genus currently includes 26 species (Cordeiro et al. 2022), with a wide range of morphologies. Consequently, determining consistent and robust diagnostic morphological characters for this genus is problematic and suggests revision is needed. Species attributed to the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wright" authorityYear="1869" box="[298,413,368,393]" class="Anthozoa" family="Isididae" genus="Keratoisis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Alcyonacea" pageId="4" pageNumber="141" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[298,413,368,393]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="141">Keratoisis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are spread throughout the cladogram of 
<bibRefCitation author="Watling, L. &amp; Heestand Saucier, E. &amp; France, S. C." box="[877,1115,368,394]" pageId="4" pageNumber="141" pagination="337 - 375" refId="ref9546" refString="Watling, L. Heestand Saucier, E. &amp; France, S. C. (2022) Towards a revision of the bamboo corals: Part 4, delineating the family Keratoisididae. Zootaxa, 5093 (3), 337 - 375. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 5093.3.4" type="journal article" year="2022">Watling et al. (2022)</bibRefCitation>
, but the 
<typeStatus box="[1215,1263,368,394]" pageId="4" pageNumber="141">type</typeStatus>
species for the genus, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wright" authorityYear="1869" box="[229,319,404,429]" class="Anthozoa" family="Isididae" genus="Keratoisis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Alcyonacea" pageId="4" pageNumber="141" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="grayi">
<emphasis box="[229,319,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="141">K. grayi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, is nested within clade D2. Based on morphological analyses and supported by genetic evidence, two new species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wright" authorityYear="1869" box="[324,439,440,465]" class="Anthozoa" family="Isididae" genus="Keratoisis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Alcyonacea" pageId="4" pageNumber="141" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[324,439,440,465]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="141">Keratoisis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were discovered in the Tasmanian material examined in this study (
<figureCitation box="[1203,1273,440,466]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[415,1180,182,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[393,1195,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Cladogram of the Keratoisididae modified from Watling et al. (2022). New taxa added in this paper are in bold lettering. Bootstrap values&gt;50 are shown above the nodes and Bayesian probability values&gt;0.5 are shown below the nodes. Major clades are referred to by the designation along the right side of the cladogram." pageId="4" pageNumber="141">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). A previously known species, 
<taxonomicName box="[332,478,476,502]" class="Anthozoa" family="Keratoisididae" genus="Onkoisis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Alcyonacea" pageId="4" pageNumber="141" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="magnifica">
<emphasis box="[332,478,476,502]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="141">K. magnifica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, is not genetically related to the 
<typeStatus box="[852,900,476,502]" pageId="4" pageNumber="141">type</typeStatus>
species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wright" authorityYear="1869" box="[1029,1144,476,501]" class="Anthozoa" family="Isididae" genus="Keratoisis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Alcyonacea" pageId="4" pageNumber="141" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1029,1144,476,501]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="141">Keratoisis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, therefore a new genus is erected below to encompass that species and a mis-identified species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Verrill" authorityYear="1883" box="[959,1060,512,538]" class="Anthozoa" family="Isididae" genus="Lepidisis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Alcyonacea" pageId="4" pageNumber="141" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[959,1060,512,538]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="141">Lepidisis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Grant, R." box="[1102,1250,511,538]" pageId="4" pageNumber="141" pagination="1 - 56" refId="ref9113" refString="Grant, R. (1976) The marine fauna of New Zealand: Isididae (Octocorallia: Gorgonacea) from New Zealand and the Antarctic. New Zealand Oceanographic Institute Memoir, 66, 1 - 56." type="journal article" year="1976">Grant (1976)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
